@realmoney Jan 03, 2023 | 11:18 AM EST DOUG KASS My First Half Outlook: No Market Disaster, Some Stock Price Appreciation But Capped by Interest Rate Levels * At my hedge fund, Seabreeze Partners, I have been patiently waiting for the right pitch - taking a lot of pitches

throughout the past year * This column is intended to provide an unemotional, balanced (and non hyperbolic) and what I hope is a realistic view of the outlook for the first six months of the new year * My overall view has been consistent for several months - that we were in

a relatively tight and range bound market * In my view and tactically speaking - today we are virtually in the middle of my anticipated S&P six months trading range of 3700-4100 * I do not share the Cassandra like short term predictions from the bearish cabal and I would not be

surprised if the first half of 2023 experienced a modest gain in stock values - and, not, as a growing consensus believes, a large drop * However, the upside is capped by a wide range of uncertainties and by the relative (against the low S&P dividend yield) and the high absolute

level of interest rates - which has produced an opportunity to deliver equity like returns with little risk * The bottom line is that we do not yet have a solid green light to buy more aggressively, but we might soon... realmoney.thestreet.com/doug… @SeabreezeLP

The violent movements in the S&P futures market (since the opening yesterday evening) is, well... FUBAR. @tomkeene @lisaabramowicz1 @ferrotv @business @cnbcfastmoney @jimcramer @ScottWapnerCNBC @carlquintanilla @riskreversal @guyadami @saraeisen
